Author: LooTz#2749
Content: When creating a chain with komodo's 51% attack protection does that protect a coin initially from pools that have over 51% of the hash power ?

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: Yes, it needs more power to attack than 51%, and even then probably fail

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: Dpowconf doesn't increase confirmations larger than 1 until chain notarize

Author: LooTz#2749
Content: cool thanks grewal for confirming

Author: hastrup#8742
Content: Sell all for easy nothing

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: @grewalsatinder ummm unless they build enough blocks that notarize to KMD right?

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: So if they could 51% attack  a chain for the minimum number of blocks before it gets written to KMD then that could then be written to BTC.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: But every notarization would be a checkpoint and they could roll back

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: In any case smart chains should be considered secure to the point they are notarized

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: It is very much like waiting for 10 min aprox for btc 1 confirmation

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: If a transaction is 1+ confirmed, it is safe

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content:
That is the important part. People need to realise that. If they do what grewalsatinder said, there is no risk. If not, you risk an attack affecting you. 
Also smart chains could pay to have notarisations more often or less often, if they're worried or not. The cost becomes a lot more if its more often though. So I believe most coins do it every 10 blocks
